data.description:
1: A malicious pop-up window appeared on the CoinMarketCap official website, and the official reminded not to connect the wallet;
2: After AguilaTrades increased its long position to 400 million for the third time, BTC fell again, and the current floating loss is 7.85 million US dollars;
3: Bloomberg analysts: The probability of approval of most spot crypto ETFs has been raised to 90% or higher;
4: Trump criticized Powell again: He may consider replacing his position and called for an immediate interest rate cut to save trillions of dollars in spending;
5: Trend Research may hold 64.25% of the total NEIRO tokens;
6: Yi Lihua responded to the high control of NEIRO: The secondary market only bought and did not sell, it was purely a bottom-fishing hope that it would become the leader;
7: Analysis: Trend Research's ETH cost is about 2,240 US dollars, with a floating profit of about 55 million US dollars;
8: Uniswap and Morpho jointly launched the Web3SOC security governance framework to improve DeFi compliance and institutional adaptability;
9: Market news: Reddit Negotiating to use Worldcoin's iris scanning device Orb;
10: A whale shorted 40,000 ETH with 10x leverage 9 days ago, with a floating profit of more than 12.15 million US dollars;
11: Fed Governor Waller sent a clear dovish signal: in favor of a rate cut in July;
12: Fed Barkin: Current data shows that there is no urgent reason to cut interest rates;
13: Pump.fun token auction postponed again to mid-July, with a valuation of approximately US$4 billion;
14: Coinbase obtained the EU encryption license and moved its EU headquarters from Ireland to Luxembourg;
15: Kraken moved its headquarters to Wyoming, saying that the state has long supported cryptocurrency policies;
16: Jupiter announced that it would suspend DAO voting until the end of 2025 because the current governance structure did not meet expectations;
17: France had its 10th encryption kidnapping case of the year, and the kidnappers demanded 5,000 euros in cash and a Ledger wallet;
18: Norwegian listed company Standard Supply The first investment was about $4.97 million to buy Bitcoin;
19: UpTop: Users who did not successfully participate in TGE will also receive airdrops;
20: Self Chain founder denies involvement in $50 million over-the-counter cryptocurrency fraud;
21: South Korean stock Bridge Biotherapeutics rose more than 20% today;
22: Senior Iranian official: Iran is ready to discuss restrictions on its uranium enrichment;
23: Bitcoin investment company Parataxis Holdings reached a 25 billion won investment agreement to go public.
